clinical_study.official_title: Use of the Zenith速 Dissection Endovascular System in the Treatment of Patients With Acute, Complicated Type B Aortic Dissection

brief_summary.textblock: The Zenith速 Dissection Clinical Trial is a clinical trial approved by US FDA to study the safety and effectiveness of the Zenith速 Dissection Endovascular System in the treatment of acute, complicate Type B aortic dissection.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants With Freedom From Major Adverse Events
primary_outcome.description: Primary safety : Major adverse events include: myocardial infarction, chronic renal insufficiency/chronic renal failure requiring dialysis, bowel ischemia, stroke, paraplegia or paraparesis, and prolonged ventilator support
Primary effectiveness endpoint is freedom from all cause mortality at 30 days

intervention.description: Instead of making a large incision in the chest, the physician makes a small incision near each hip to insert, and guides the study device(s) into place in the aorta.

facility.name: Hospital of the University of Pennsylvania

certain_agreements.restrictive_agreement: The only disclosure restriction on the PI is that the sponsor can review results communications prior to public release and can embargo communications regarding trial results for a period that is more than 60 days but less than or equal to 180 days. The sponsor cannot require changes to the communication and cannot extend the embargo.
